id: pm-gusd
title: Enforce telemetry capture_level setting in runtime event collection
description: capture_level (minimal/redacted/max) is stored in settings but not enforced. The runtime always collects max-level data regardless of the setting.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "audit:2026-04-26",pm-cli,privacy,telemetry
created_at: "2026-04-26T14:52:26.308Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-26T19:59:42.146Z"
deadline: "2026-05-10T14:52:26.308Z"
author: audit-agent
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: "capture_level minimal: only command name and duration. redacted: current behavior. max: full payload."
parent: pm-lnq3
resolution: Implemented capture-aware telemetry payload builders and sanitization routing so capture_level now controls collected fields and redaction depth.
expected_result: minimal capture_level records only essential command outcome metadata while redacted and max modes preserve intended detail boundaries.
actual_result: Telemetry runtime now emits minimal payloads when configured and retains redacted/max behaviors with dedicated unit coverage and passing linked tests.
